          <td bgcolor="" valign="top" width="1"><img src="/lotr/gfx/trans_header1.gif" width="0" height="2" vspace="0" hspace="0" border="0"></td>
          <td bgcolor="" valign="top"><!-- #BeginEditable "Body" --> 
            <table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
<tr><td width=1><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/bro_01.gif" width=6 height=6></td><td width=100% background="/lotr/gfx/mom/bro_02.gif"></td>
<td width=1><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/bro_03.gif" width=6 height=6></td></tr>
<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/bro_04.gif"><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/clear.gif" height=35 width=1></td>
<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/bro_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/bro_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Eugene, OR 6/27/02<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(5.00)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=3367'>Nathan "Bib Fortuna" Russell</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=3367&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> June 28, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Well, this tournament was the exclamation point on a long day of being at Addictive Behaviors. I spent the first 4 hours of the day (starting at 11) sorting hundreds, possibly thousands of Star Wars cards into the store&#39;s binders, backstock and the penny box. Needless to say, I was a little exhausted when I got off work at 3. At that point, a new LOTR player named Mike was playing a pickup game against another player, whose name I can&#39;t remember. I had been teaching Mike how to play all week, so I tried to coach him through the game. Although he lost, I think he learned a lot.<br>
<br>
Anyway, Mike, myself and the other guy decided to do a pickup game of multiplayer, just for the heck of it, as I had never played multiplayer before. My deck is a large fellowship, Gondor, Elf archery combined with Moria archery. Mike&#39;s is a Dwarf/Sauron deck, and the other guy&#39;s is very similar to mine.<br>
<br>
Mike bids 3, the other guy bids 2, and I bid 1, and we play in that order. Both of them only move once on their turn, but I feel a little bold and double move to site 3, at the cost of losing my Arwen, which wasn&#39;t very fun. But it was worth it to get a jump start on them.<br>
<br>
When we get to Site 5, Mike decides to double move to Site 6, and we carefully total all the twilight we have, and drop the Cave Troll and the Witch King and he gets eliminated.<br>
<br>
Me and the other guy vie for a little bit, then I stop moving at Site 7 while he&#39;s at Site 6. Since we&#39;re in a 3 person game, our move limit is 3, so he decides to try a triple move to Site 9. He used Thror&#39;s Map to play Shores Of Nen Hithoel for Site 8, as opposed to my Brown Lands, and I still couldn&#39;t get 5 Orcs out to stop the triple move. He directs some archery to kill off my Orcs, then moves to Site 9, and I can&#39;t get enough minions out to stop him, despite having They Are Coming in play, and drawing extra cards with the Summit Of Amon Hen.<br>
<br>
Following that game, I wandered outside to get some food (as it was around 5 in the evening and I hadn&#39;t eaten since breakfast), and the other guy stayed behind to help Mike&#39;s deck some more. Unfortunately, he couldn&#39;t stick around for the actual tournament, since he had to go play some D&D with some friends.<br>
<br>
Anyway, on to the actual tournament.<br>
<br>
6:00 rolls around and we have 4 players: Myself, Mike, Mark Apker and Kirk Powell. We get a call from James on the road, saying he&#39;s bringing two others, bringing our total up to 7. For the 8th player, we recruit Jon Paul, another Addictive Behaviors employee. Our first game finally starts at around 6:45.<br>
<br>
As I stated before, my deck was a large fellowship, Gondor, Elf archery combined with Moria archery.<br>
<br>
Game 1 vs Mike:<br>
<br>
I felt kinda guilty about playing Mike, since I knew his deck more or less inside out. But I pushed those thoughts out of my mind and proceeded to play the best game I could. He bids high and goes first. His starting fellowship is Gimli DOTMR and Farin, while mine is Greenleaf and Arwen. He gets Gandalf TGP and Fror out on the first turn, then moves to my Midgewater Marshes, exerting Frodo. I have 10 twilight, so I just drop a Moria Archer Troop for 8 and end my shadow phase. He takes an archery wound on Frodo, then Gimli fights and takes 1. He chooses to stop there. On my Fellowship phase, I drop Gandalf and Sam, then I move on, exerting both my Hobbits. He drops an Orc Soldier and an Orc Soldiers. I choose not to direct my archery, and just send Gandalf and Arwen against his guys. He exerts to wound Arwen, and she takes a wound for losing, as does Gandalf. I decide to move again to the Council Courtyard, and he succeeds in dropping another Orc Soldier on me. He uses Hate to kill Arwen, then I direct archery to kill the two wounded Orcs. Gandalf takes another wound in the fighting.<br>
<br>
He doesn&#39;t deploy any new companions this turn, and I use my 5 twilight to play a Goblin Marksman, dealing 2 more wounds on his guys. On my turn, I heal up and play Aragorn and his Bow, then I move on to the Moria Lake, exerting Frodo once again. He can only afford one Orc, and my two archers kill him off. I stop there. On his turn, he gets Sam out, and I drop some Runners and more archers to deal another few points of damage, although he finally gets some Dwarf strength-boosting events to make him finally win some skirmishes.<br>
<br>
I luckily get out Boromir and Armor move to Site 5, and he naturally brings out the Balrog, and Boromir jumps in front and takes 2, and I move again, and I direct some archery to kill off the two Orcs he plays at Valley Of The Silverlode. He gets a pair of Dwarf Guards out, then moves to the Bridge, where I drop a Runner, a Bowman, a Scavengers and, of course, the Balrog. The Guards jump in front of the Balrog, but he chooses not to move again. I double move to Site 8, newly reinforced with Haldir + Bow, and my archery kills off his Orcs. He moves to Site 6, and I play a few minions, then I move to Site 9 for the relatively easy win.<br>
<br>
Pros: Seeing how far Mike has progressed as a player in this past week.<br>
Cons: I made a mistake and allowed Arwen to get killed early.<br>
<br>
Game 2 vs Kirk&#39;s Elf archery Mirror/Sauron Nazgul deck:<br>
<br>
He bids high and goes first, using the same starting Fellowship as me. He gets out Galadriel and Orophin, but no Mirror yet. Since he has Green Dragon as a starting site, he gets out Sam and removes those burdens. Arwen also gets a Bow. He moves, exerting Frodo, and I drop an Archer Troop plus a Bowman. Legolas exerts to kill the Bowman, Frodo takes an archery wound, and Arwen fights the Troop and loses. He stays there. I get Aragorn, Boromir and Haldir out, then I move. He plays Cantea, and Legolas exerts twice to hurt him, then Arwen + Defiance kills him off. I move again, and surprise surprise, it&#39;s the Ford Of Bruinen. He plays Twilight Attea for free, plus an Orc Hunter. Arwen fights Attea and takes 1, then Aragorn fights the Hunter and takes 2.<br>
<br>
He moves again, and I use the Ford to play my non-Twilight Witch King for 3, plus a Marksman. That&#39;s enough to kill off Arwen (she seems to die early a lot, huh?) and exhaust Legolas.<br>
<br>
I heal up and I get out Gandalf and I use Thror&#39;s Map to get out the Great Chasm, anticipating his next turn. Aragorn fights his lone Orc and takes 2 again. When I draw up, I get the Cave Troll, two runners and a marksman. He plays the Mirror and Sting, then he Stings my hand to see what I have. Naturally, he then tries to use the Mirror to eliminate my minions, but he only nabs Free Peoples cards both times. I drop all my guys and Frodo gets smacked.<br>
<br>
Pros: Finally beating Kirk.<br>
Cons: Arwen died early YET AGAIN?!<br>
<br>
Game 3 vs James&#39; Elf archery/Moria archery deck:<br>
<br>
Once again, a deck that&#39;s almost exactly like mine. He bids 5 and goes first, using the Prancing Pony to get Aragorn. He also plays Sam. I don&#39;t have many minions in my hand, so I just play a Moria Scout + a runner. They die easily, and he moves again. This time I succeed in getting a Marksman out.<br>
<br>
I have an insane Fellowship hand: I play Aragorn via the Prancing Pony, then Gandalf, Rumil, Gimli and an Elven Bow on Arwen. I double move to site 3, easily eliminating his minions with my archery + Swordsman and Defiance.<br>
<br>
The details of the middle part of the game escape me at the moment, but I also got out Boromir and Sam before I entered the Mines, and his Aragorn and Arwen got their Bows. I also got out They Are Coming. I get to Site 8 (Brown Lands), while he&#39;s at 7. He moves to 8 on his turn, and I drop several archers on him, exhausting everyone. He chooses to move to Site 9, after defeating all of my Brown Lands minions with archery + combat. I draw 3 extra cards with Summit, then I proceed to play my minions. 2 Runners, a Flankers and a Scavengers in my hand go down, and I use the Scavengers&#39; scimitar to draw another card. I then use They Are Coming 3 times to get a Moria Scout, an Archer Commander and an Archer Troop. He directs and kills the commander, then he takes an archery wound, killing Sam. The Flankers fight Aragorn, the Scavengers fight Arwen, and the Troop fights Legolas, leaving everyone else to overwhelm Frodo. <br>
<br>
Pros: That was one of the funnest games I have ever played. Things looked grim for me at the end until I remembered I had They Are Coming in play.<br>
Cons: Not remembering a lot of the details of the game.<br>
<br>
Game 4 vs Mark&#39;s Dwarf/Sauron deck<br>
<br>
We each bid 5, and he wins the dice roll to go first. He starts the Pony and gets Aragorn, Sam and Farin out, in addition to his starting 3. At this point, I&#39;m wondering where my Enquea is, but I don&#39;t get him out on the first turn. He double moves to Site 3 without any Enquea appearances.<br>
<br>
I also get 6 companions out on the first turn, and he likewise cannot find his Enquea. I catch up with him at Site 3. On his turn, he puts some Bracers on Farin and moves to Site 4, where my Enquea finally makes his appearance. But since Farin had his Bracers, Enquea didn&#39;t deal enough damage to kill anyone off. Although it&#39;s just as well, since the Balrog killed Farin on the next turn.<br>
<br>
I also don&#39;t recall any additional details of this game until the end. I get into a similar situation as I did with James. He moves to Site 9, where I draw 3 more with Summit. The only difference is that I had no They Are Coming. I assign 2 runners to Frodo, and he plays a Hobbit Stealth to boost Frodo&#39;s strength to 6, making him not overwhelmed.<br>
<br>
Pros: Getting out my Enquea at the right time.<br>
Cons: Not killing anyone with Enquea.<br>
<br>
I ended up going 3-1, as did Mark and James. But since Mark had taken a Bye in the second round (Jon Paul dropped), he didn&#39;t have enough points to put him ahead of me. As for James, he finished in 3rd, since everyone he beat had a small point differential. I placed first, followed by Mark. <br></font></blockquote><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?id=3786&view=1'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
